				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12308318/scp-4609#post-4865450</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 08 Jan 2021 21:24:39 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ISNorden</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6966599</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Exactly: living things get electrocuted (killed by electricity), and wardrobes aren't alive. (Yes, SCP-002 and similar &quot;oddly living&quot; entities exist; but nothing in this write-up implies that #4609 is one.)</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12308318#post-4330701</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12308318/scp-4609#post-4330701</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 14 Aug 2019 19:03:52 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ProfessorCarvalho</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5316340</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I think having someone from the Foundation knowing about it is a great way of knowing that absolutely no knowledge of it spreads. If there was ever any extraneous record of the object and someone got knowledge of the wardrobe, the person from the Foundation would instantly die, and the Foundation would know that they have to send someone else to the site, killing the other person but preventing a breach.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12308318#post-4330228</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12308318/scp-4609#post-4330228</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 14 Aug 2019 07:49:58 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ManyCookies</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2110511</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Oof, that's a rough anticlimactic ending for poor Ogden.</p> <p>If the cabinet has no way of propagating info about itself, a successor seems like an unnecessary waste of a trustworthy personnel. Why not barricade the site and post a warning about &quot;memetic hazards&quot; or whatnot (lord knows the Foundation has a few sites like that)? Or have the successor drop it off/bury it somewhere anonymous and take amnestics afterwards?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
